course.subject: COMP
course.name: Competitive Programming in Cybersecurity III
course.description: The course will be offered as an 2-credit course in the Fall semester. A good proportion of senior student members who have finished COMP4901O in a previous Spring semester could join the course in the Fall semester after getting instructor consent. They will further enhance their leadership and practical knowledge by taking part in the experience sharing and training of the freshly joined COMP4901N students. The students will get 1 credit for successfully completing COMP4901P. Instructor's approval is required.
